.Dd December 15, 2006
.Dt SCTP_FREEPADDRS 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sctp_freepaddrs ,
.Nm sctp_freeladdrs
.Nd release the memory returned from a previous call
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In sys/socket.h
.In netinet/sctp.h
.Ft void
.Fn sctp_freepaddrs "struct sockaddr *"
.Ft void
.Fn sctp_freeladdrs "struct sockaddr *"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn sctp_freepaddrs
and
.Fn sctp_freeladdrs
functions are used to release the memory allocated by previous
calls to
.Fn sctp_getpaddrs
or
.Fn sctp_getladdrs
respectively.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
none.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sctp_getladdrs 3 ,
.Xr sctp_getpaddrs 3 ,
.Xr sctp 4
